   =20
      Vivek Ramaswamy
   =20
 =20

A general model would be:
=09If you found and run a biotech company and it develops a drug that cures=
 Alzheimer=E2=80=99s disease, that will be worth, I dunno, pick a number, s=
ay $10 billion to you personally.=09If you found and run a biotech company =
and it is developing a drug that has a 10% chance of curing Alzheimer=E2=80=
=99s disease, that is worth, in expectation,=C2=A0$1 billion to you persona=
lly. Once the clinical trials are completed, then it is worth either $0, wi=
th 90% probability, or $10 billion, with 10% probability, but=C2=A0before t=
he trials its expected value is $1 billion.=09If you can find someone to bu=
y, say, 20% of your stake for $200 million, before the trials are completed=
, then you have $200 million no matter what.=09If then the drug cures Alzhe=
imer=E2=80=99s, you (1) have $8.2 billion and (2) cured Alzheimer=E2=80=99s=
, and you live out the rest of your days as a billionaire drug magnate, phi=
lanthropist, etc.=09If the drug does=C2=A0not=C2=A0cure Alzheimer=E2=80=99s=
, you (1) have $200 million and (2) kind of need to find something else to =
do with your life. Run for president I guess?

Anyway here is  a New York Times article about Vivek Ramaswamy, who did not=
 cure Alzheimer=E2=80=99s, but who did take a couple hundred million dollar=
s off the table while running Roivant Sciences Ltd. and is now running for =
president. =E2=80=9CIn an interview, Mr. Ramaswamy said he cashed out only =
to make room for [another investor], not to hedge his bets ahead of intepir=
dine=E2=80=99s clinical trial,=E2=80=9D but honestly I think it would be we=
ird=C2=A0not=C2=A0to hedge your bets if you could. Ramaswamy=E2=80=99s upsi=
de, just before that clinical trial, was that he could be a billionaire who=
 cured Alzheimer=E2=80=99s, his downside, after that sale, was that at leas=
t he could be a self-funded presidential candidate. Either way is fine! It=
=E2=80=99s a good hedge.
(Disclosure: I think Ramaswamy  once asked me to write a book about him? =
=E2=80=9CA spokeswoman for Ramaswamy=E2=80=99s campaign said he unsuccessfu=
lly tried to recruit Levine to join Roivant but doesn=E2=80=99t recall aski=
ng him to write a book.=E2=80=9D Something like that, anyway.)

