<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last year my friend Mary Childs <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31919120.257399/aHR0cHM6Ly91cy5t=
YWNtaWxsYW4uY29tL2Jvb2tzLzk3ODEyNTAxMjA4NTQvdGhlYm9uZGtpbmc/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB2eb68647" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> published a book</a> about Bill Gross called=
 <em>The Bond King: How One Man Made a Market, Built an Empire, and Lost It=
 All</em>.=C2=A0The market that Gross built was the investment-grade bond m=
arket. In the olden days, when Gross started out, the way bonds worked was =
that companies sold bonds, and insurance companies bought them and held the=
m to maturity.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/31919120.257399/aHR0cHM6Ly9ib29rcy5nb29nbGUuY29tL2Jvb2tzP2lkPXdwb09FQUFBU=
UJBSiZwZz1QVDI5JmxwZz1QVDI5JmRxPSUyMkdyb3NzK2ZvdW5kK2hpbXNlbGYrd2l0aCt1bmlu=
dGVyZXN0aW5nK2pvYnMrbGlrZStjbGlwcGluZytib25kK2NvdXBvbnMraW4rUGFjaWZpYytNdXR=
1YWwlRTIlODAlOTlzK3ZhdWx0LCtzbmlwcGluZyt0aGUrbGl0dGxlK3RhZ3Mrb2ZmK3RoZStib3=
R0b20rb2YrY29ycG9yYXRlK2NlcnRpZmljYXRlcythbmQrbWFpbGluZyt0aGVtK2luK2Zvcitpb=
nRlcmVzdCtwYXltZW50cyUyMiZzb3VyY2U9Ymwmb3RzPU1WNlNmUU1QZ2Emc2lnPUFDZlUzVTBM=
TjNFWmlZY3NERVRtblk4WUFNTmtrQnFpaFEmaGw9ZW4mc2E9WCZ2ZWQ9MmFoVUtFd2lUaS1DWTV=
1UF9BaFV6bFlrRUhVTkhCQ0VRNkFGNkJBZ05FQU0jdj1vbmVwYWdlJnE9JTIyR3Jvc3MlMjBmb3=
