<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A general model would be:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you found and run a biotech compan=
y and it develops a drug that cures Alzheimer=E2=80=99s disease, that will =
be worth, I dunno, pick a number, say $10 billion to you personally.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you found and run a biotech company=
 and it is developing a drug that has a 10% chance of curing Alzheimer=E2=
=80=99s disease, that is worth, in expectation,=C2=A0$1 billion to you pers=
onally. Once the clinical trials are completed, then it is worth either $0,=
 with 90% probability, or $10 billion, with 10% probability, but=C2=A0<em>b=
efore </em>the trials its expected value is $1 billion.</li>=09<li style=3D=
"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you can find someone to buy, say, 20% of your stak=
e for $200 million, before the trials are completed, then you have $200 mil=
lion no matter what.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If then the d=
rug cures Alzheimer=E2=80=99s, you (1) have $8.2 billion and (2) cured Alzh=
eimer=E2=80=99s, and you live out the rest of your days as a billionaire dr=
ug magnate, philanthropist, etc.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I=
f the drug does=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>cure Alzheimer=E2=80=99s, you (1) ha=
ve $200 million and (2) kind of need to find something else to do with your=
 life. Run for president I guess?</li>
</ol>
